{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1677775106,"nonce":"CJjpOa7oA4kBX1Nvyo7m1Z/WDr0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh85Wjmxi","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/327#issuecomment-1452174434"},"message":"If we're looking for a cross-platform solution, letting the user pick how their credentials are stored and using `git-credential` is actually what I'd argue for, since that is a) available in Git, requiring no additional user-managed dependency, and b) not limiting the user to supported secret backends (e.g. a particular keyring).\n\nI do not have `gnome-keyring` installed, and have no desire to install it just so I can use it for managing my `git-bug` credentials -- I'd much prefer to use my existing password store.","files":null}]}